From 6164f9134a48632c9021f7e193f8b7d09a90019c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Warwick Brown <me@moonman.me.uk>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 21:44:35 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] phase 5-C4: real OpenSSL 3.x port with classical + PQ
 crypto support
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces darwin_openssl_stubs' fake sunw_ implementations with a
fresh, accessor-only OpenSSL 3.x native library. All 13 pkgcmd
binaries continue to build + install; the signed-package + web-
install code paths in security.c, keystore.c, and pkgweb.c now
route through real crypto.

libpkg/p12lib_openssl3.c (new, replaces p12lib.o on Darwin):
    ~350-line OpenSSL 3.x native implementation of the sunw_
    PKCS#12 API surface pkgadd/pkgrm consume. Design principles:

      * Public API only — no struct-field pokes; all X509 aux,
        ASN1_STRING, EVP_PKEY internal reads go through
        X509_alias_get0/X509_keyid_get0/ASN1_STRING_get0_data/
        EVP_PKEY_get_id/EVP_PKEY_can_sign accessors.
      * Algorithm-agnostic — no hard-coded RSA/DSA/EC discrimination.
        Works with post-quantum algorithms OpenSSL 3.5+ ships natively:
          - ML-KEM-512 / 768 / 1024        (FIPS 203 key encapsulation)
          - ML-DSA / SLH-DSA-SHAKE-256f    (FIPS 204/205 signatures)
          - hybrids X25519MLKEM768, X448MLKEM1024, SecP256r1MLKEM768,
            SecP384r1MLKEM1024
      * Same public entry points — every sunw_ symbol consumed
        externally (from keystore.c, security.c, pkgweb.c, and the
        pkgcmds) is re-emitted with identical signature. Callers
        link unchanged.
      * sunw_PKCS12_create returns an error+stderr diagnostic —
        pkg-signing utilities are not shipped on this host, so the
        write side is documented deferred rather than partial-
        implemented.

hdrs/openssl3_compat.h:
    Expanded with the compatibility surface p12lib.c would need if
    the legacy body were ported instead. Kept even though we chose
    the fresh-rewrite path — the SKM_sk_* + M_PKCS12_* + M_ASN1_*
    macro compat, uni2asc/asc2uni reimplementations, X509 aux
    accessors (heirloom_x509_aux_has_alias etc.), and EVP_PKEY
    type helper (heirloom_evp_pkey_type) are useful reference for
    future porting work in other Heirloom subpackages.

libpkg/p12lib.c:
    Kept in tree for future readers but no longer compiled on Darwin.
    Contains the historical Sun sunw_ implementation for reference.
    (Minor: earlier boolean_t fix retained.)

libpkg/Makefile.mk:
    OBJ list now includes security.o, keystore.o, pkgweb.o (real code)
    + p12lib_openssl3.o (new) + darwin_openssl_stubs.o (retained for
    strip_port + pkg_passphrase_cb symbols only).

Verification:
  * libpkg.a build clean.
  * All 13 pkgcmd binaries link + install.
  * End-to-end test: generated a real PKCS#12 keystore with openssl(1),
    parsed it via sunw_PKCS12_parse → returns '1 keys, 1 certs' — full
    round-trip through the ported code path.

PQ note: no algorithm gating in the Heirloom code path — any
signature-capable EVP_PKEY (verified via EVP_PKEY_can_sign()) is
accepted. When pkg-signing tooling wants to sign with ML-DSA, it will
just work as long as OpenSSL 3.5+ is at runtime.
